data.chText: 可钦佩的；值得赞赏的；令人羡慕的
data.enText: having qualities that you admire and respect

data.chText: 她对工作的奉献精神可钦可佩。
data.enText: Her dedication to her work was admirable.

data.chText: 他阐述观点明确，值得赞赏。
data.enText: He made his points with admirable clarity.
Joe coped admirably with a difficult situation.

tr: deserving of the highest esteem or admiration
example: his taste was impeccable, his health admirable
among her many admirable qualities are generosity and graciousness

value.def: An admirable quality or action is one that deserves to be praised and admired.

example.tran: 贝顿是个令人钦佩的人物。

example.ex: The film tells its story with admirable economy.
example.tran: 这部电影叙事简练，令人叹服。

value.tran: 令人钦佩的；值得赞赏的

example.ex: Peter had dealt admirably with the sudden questions about Keith...
example.tran: 彼得对突如其来的有关基思的问题应答自如，令人叹服。
约翰斯通的研究涉猎很广，让人钦佩。
